<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<body>
	<style>
	.font_1 {
		background-color: black;
		color: yellow;
		font-size: large;
	}
	.font_2 {
		background-color: darkblue;
		color: white;
		font-size: medium;
	}
	.My_Style {
		background-color: red;
		color: white;
		font-size: 30px;
		font-weight: bolder;
	}
	</style>
	<h2 class="font_1">This h2&#8209;element is styled per class attribute font_1</h2>
	<h3 class="font_2">This h3&#8209;element is styled per class attribute font_2</h3>
	<h4 class="font_1">Even though this is an h4&#8209;element, it is style the same
	as the h2&#8209;element becaues we pointed to the class attribute font_1</h4>
	<p class="My_Style">This is a test to see if the My_Style attribute 
	tag applies to this p class. </p>
	<p class="My_Style">This is a test to see if I can put more than one space between
	two sentances.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Did this work? I'm sure it did.. </p>
	</body>
</html>